  "title": "Senior Tunnel Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Duties and Responsibility:</strong></u></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>The Senior Tunnel Engineer is responsible for, but not limited to the following:</p><p>1. Provide planning of tunnelling operation from safety, quality, and productivity viewpoint.</p><p>2. Provide engineering supervision to bored tunnelling operation, including final ring selection and\nselection of key.</p><p>3. Ensure the work is done in compliant with the protocol established for the project.</p><p>4. Whole related Tunnel Engineering Work.</p><p><strong>Qualifications/Job Experience</strong>:</p><p>· Minimum 8 years of engineering experience after tertiary education in relevant field</p><p>· At least 5 years of experience in construction supervision of tunnelling works of similar scale, complexity\nand nature of work.</p><p>· TBM (Tunnel Boring Machine) experience</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent.</p><p>· Experience in handling tunnelling projects.</p><p>· Ability to work under compressed air.</p>",
